To further elucidate the effects of APTA on the trap distribution and energy, we carried out thermal admittance spectroscopy (TAS) measurements. For a semiconductor, the defect activation energy (Ea) approximates the distance between the defect state energy level and the valence band [35, 43]. Herein, TAS measurements for the devices (Fig. 5a) without and (Fig. 5b) with APTA are executed at gradient temperatures (250 to 320 K) in the dark from 5 to 10,000 Hz. Figure S11 displays the derivative image of the capacitance–frequency spectra. The relationship between characteristic transition angular frequency ω0 and Ea follows Eq. 2:2ω0=βT2e-EakBT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
