				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$V_{OC} = \frac{{nk_{B} T}}{q}\ln \left( {{\Phi }_{ph} } \right)$$\end{document}where n is the ideal factor and q is the elementary charge. Through linear fitting, the slopes of the devices without and with APTA are 1.86 (kBT/q) and 1.37 (kBT/q), respectively. An ideal factor closer to 1 for the APTA-incorporated PSC indicated that trap-assisted recombination is effectively inhibited because of the reduction of trap density, which is consistent with the previous experimental results.
